### Multithreading

C++11 introduced a standardized multithreading library (`<thread>`) for concurrent programming.

---

### Creating Threads

```cpp
#include <thread>

void worker() {
  cout << "Working in thread";
}

int main() {
  thread t(worker);  // Start thread
  t.join();          // Wait for thread to finish
}
```

---

### Thread with Arguments

```cpp
void printSum(int a, int b) {
  cout << "Sum: " << (a + b);
}

thread t(printSum, 5, 3);
t.join();
```

---

### Mutex and Lock

```cpp
#include <mutex>

mutex mtx;
int sharedCounter = 0;

void increment() {
  lock_guard<mutex> lock(mtx);  // RAII lock
  sharedCounter++;
}
```

---

### Synchronization Primitives

| Primitive | Description | Header |
|-----------|-------------|--------|
| `mutex` | Basic mutual exclusion | `<mutex>` |
| `recursive_mutex` | Reentrant mutex | `<mutex>` |
| `timed_mutex` | Mutex with timeout | `<mutex>` |
| `lock_guard` | RAII mutex wrapper | `<mutex>` |
| `unique_lock` | Flexible RAII lock | `<mutex>` |
| `condition_variable` | Thread waiting | `<condition_variable>` |
| `atomic` | Lock-free operations | `<atomic>` |

---

### Atomic Operations

```cpp
#include <atomic>

atomic<int> counter(0);

void increment() {
  counter.fetch_add(1);  // Thread-safe increment
}
```

---

### std::async (Higher-Level)

```cpp
#include <future>

int compute(int x) {
  return x * x;
}

auto future = async(launch::async, compute, 5);
int result = future.get();  // 25
```

---

> **Key Point:** Always join or detach threads. Use `lock_guard` or `unique_lock` for exception-safe mutex locking. Prefer `std::async` for simple parallel tasks over manual thread management.

codeExample:
#include <iostream>
#include <thread>
#include <mutex>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

mutex mtx;

void printWork(int id) {
  lock_guard<mutex> lock(mtx);
  cout << "Thread " << id << " working" << endl;
}

int main() {
  vector<thread> threads;

  for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    threads.emplace_back(printWork, i);
  }

  for (auto& t : threads) {
    t.join();
  }

  cout << "All threads completed" << endl;
  return 0;
}
